WEBVTT

00:06.439 --> 00:10.102
<i>(I LIKE WHAT YOU SAY</i> BY NADA SURF
PLAYING ON SOUNDTRACK)

00:10.176 --> 00:13.304
Ravens win! Mommy, Ravens win.

00:13.380 --> 00:18.079
Haley. That's weird, I thought Mommy
would've beat us home by now.

00:18.151 --> 00:19.812
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

00:19.986 --> 00:20.975
Hey.

00:21.054 --> 00:24.023
Nathan, hi. I'm so sorry.
You got Jamie, right?

00:24.190 --> 00:27.318
Yeah, yeah. What happened?
Where are you?

00:27.394 --> 00:29.862
Oh, I got locked in the library
with Lindsey and Peyton.

00:29.929 --> 00:33.831
I missed the whole game. I'll fill you in on
all the gory details as soon as I get home.

00:33.900 --> 00:35.128
I'm on my way, okay?

00:35.201 --> 00:37.431
All right, well, I'm just about to
put Jamie to bed,

00:37.504 --> 00:39.665
and then I'm gonna take a quick shower.

00:39.739 --> 00:42.640
Oh, and Haley, I love you.

00:43.777 --> 00:46.177
- I love you, too.
- Bye.

00:48.114 --> 00:50.344
Do I really have to go to bed, Daddy?

00:50.417 --> 00:53.215
Yep. PJs, brush teeth, bed. Five minutes.

00:53.286 --> 00:56.119
- Come on, chop-chop.
- Do I have to wear PJs?

00:56.189 --> 00:57.781
Can't I sleep in this?

00:58.458 --> 01:01.222
Okay, but just for tonight, all right?

01:01.294 --> 01:03.728
- Now, come on. Let's go.
- Awesome.

01:03.797 --> 01:07.392
<i>They say learn from your mistakes</i>

01:07.867 --> 01:10.961
<i>That's not always the case</i>

01:11.704 --> 01:14.730
<i>I see them and I understand</i>

01:15.108 --> 01:17.736
<i>How I made them again and again</i>

01:17.811 --> 01:21.269
<i>They say you have to have somebody</i>

01:21.581 --> 01:24.379
<i>They say you have to be someone's</i>

01:24.751 --> 01:27.777
<i>They say if you're not lonely alone</i>

01:29.122 --> 01:32.250
- Missed you tonight.
- Oh, I missed you, too.

01:32.325 --> 01:34.520
Whoa, Carrie! Carrie, what are you doing?
This is not okay.

01:34.594 --> 01:35.788
You have to get out of here.

01:35.862 --> 01:38.592
It's okay, Nathan. I love you, too.

01:38.665 --> 01:40.724
What are you talking about?
You think I love you?

01:40.800 --> 01:43.633
Carrie, you have to get out of here.
Here, take this. Go.

01:43.703 --> 01:44.965
Get out of the shower.

01:45.038 --> 01:47.563
Carrie, get out of this bathroom right now.

01:50.543 --> 01:53.808
Haley, this... Oh, my God.
This... This isn't this, okay?

01:53.880 --> 01:55.507
I swear to you, I didn't...

01:55.582 --> 01:58.107
Look, I haven't... Carrie, tell her.

01:59.018 --> 02:01.953
Nathan loves me and I love him back.

02:03.123 --> 02:06.559
I want you to get the hell out of my house.
Right now!

02:06.826 --> 02:08.020
Haley, look, I know this must look...

02:08.094 --> 02:09.390
You get out, too.

02:09.461 --> 02:11.555
- Look, I didn't...
- Get out!

02:13.000 --> 02:19.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:23.343 --> 02:26.176
Oh, I'm sorry,
I must be in the wrong office.

02:26.246 --> 02:29.181
No, wait, that's me, Peyton Sawyer,
label president.

02:29.516 --> 02:30.813
TouchÃ©.

02:31.251 --> 02:32.741
What are you doing here, John?

02:32.819 --> 02:35.219
The big corporate label finally fire you?

02:35.355 --> 02:38.119
I happened to catch this new artist's
live performance

02:38.191 --> 02:40.819
that just went completely viral online.

02:41.094 --> 02:44.325
Perhaps you know her? Mia Catalano?

02:45.098 --> 02:46.690
She's my artist, John.

02:49.235 --> 02:52.534
It's a pretty big office for such
a small label, don't you think?

02:52.839 --> 02:54.272
Well, I've got a good act.

02:54.340 --> 02:57.639
And that's one more than you've got
at your great big label.

02:58.178 --> 03:00.078
It's good to see you, Sawyer.

03:00.713 --> 03:03.841
By the way, what are you feeling
about the first single?

03:03.950 --> 03:05.417
<i>Only Fooling Myself?</i>

03:06.653 --> 03:09.053
<i>(ONL YFOOLING</i> MYSELFPLAYING)

03:09.122 --> 03:10.714
John, stay away from Mia.

03:10.790 --> 03:12.815
Let me ask you something, Peyton.

03:13.426 --> 03:17.385
If a great song is recorded,
but nobody gets a chance to hear it,

03:17.463 --> 03:18.987
does it really exist?

03:19.199 --> 03:23.431
<i>One day I'll turn around</i>
<i>And see your hand reach out</i>

03:23.503 --> 03:24.492
<i>I'm only fooling myself</i>

03:24.604 --> 03:25.696
Hey.

03:25.772 --> 03:26.864
Hey, Peyton, check it out.

03:26.940 --> 03:29.238
Haley made the finished version sound
so much better than the demo.

03:29.309 --> 03:30.606
- Mia...
- And you were so right.

03:30.677 --> 03:33.043
<i>Only Fooling Myself</i>
is definitely the single.

03:33.112 --> 03:35.603
Mia, I need to ask you a question, okay?

03:35.682 --> 03:38.583
Were you approached by
a record executive named John Knight?

03:38.651 --> 03:41.085
You mean that creepy old guy
who said he used to be your boss?

03:41.154 --> 03:44.954
- No wonder you left LA.
- No, no, this is serious. What did he say?

03:45.725 --> 03:47.852
Nothing.
He said he saw my MySpace video

03:47.927 --> 03:49.554
and that he wanted to hear
the whole record.

03:49.629 --> 03:51.221
Is that all he said?

03:52.532 --> 03:54.966
Mia, come on. What else did he say?

03:55.835 --> 03:57.496
He said I made a big mistake
in signing with you,

03:57.570 --> 04:00.266
and you don't have
the experience to launch me.

04:01.474 --> 04:05.171
<i>(HERE GOES SOMETHING</i> BY NADA SURF
PLAYING ON SOUNDTRACK)

04:10.750 --> 04:13.344
Hey, handsome. Peyton in her office?

04:13.419 --> 04:15.284
She was. Just took off.

04:15.355 --> 04:16.652
Looked like she was on a mission.

04:16.723 --> 04:18.213
She wasn't armed, was she?

04:18.291 --> 04:20.815
I don't think so,
but I didn't get a chance to pat her down.

04:20.892 --> 04:22.884
Oh. Easy, tiger.

04:24.530 --> 04:27.260
Is it too early for a Brooke Davis
on the rocks?

04:28.067 --> 04:30.092
Suit yourself. I just pour them.

04:31.938 --> 04:33.929
You know something,
I think I missed my calling.

04:34.007 --> 04:35.065
Really? How's that?

04:35.141 --> 04:37.666
Should have gone into
the clothing design business.

04:37.744 --> 04:41.009
If you can run a multi-million-dollar
company from a barstool,

04:41.080 --> 04:45.414
while sipping a.m. Cocktails,
how hard can it be?

04:45.485 --> 04:47.715
Plenty hard. You have no idea.

04:48.554 --> 04:50.078
That your story?

04:50.290 --> 04:52.758
Don't write checks you can't cash, buddy.

04:53.159 --> 04:55.354
I'd be happy to whisk you up
to New York anytime

04:55.428 --> 04:58.659
and show you how impressive and
complicated it all really is, bartender boy,

04:58.731 --> 05:01.791
but, if I did, who would tend to the bar?

05:04.337 --> 05:07.829
Flights leave on the hour, so, I dare you.

05:08.941 --> 05:12.502
All right. You're on, Brooke Davis.

05:13.046 --> 05:14.604
Okay.

05:42.675 --> 05:44.575
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

05:50.983 --> 05:52.575
So you've heard?

05:52.652 --> 05:55.348
Haley kicked me out.
I need a place to stay.

05:58.858 --> 06:00.325
What is that?

06:01.561 --> 06:02.823
It's Dan.

06:04.163 --> 06:05.528
He's up for parole.

06:17.276 --> 06:19.176
Supposed to be a smiley face.

06:19.245 --> 06:21.179
- What?
- Where's Nanny Carrie?

06:21.247 --> 06:23.112
She knows how I like them.

06:24.417 --> 06:26.180
Nanny Carrie is not home right now,

06:26.252 --> 06:29.688
and it's probably gonna be a little while
before she comes back.

06:29.756 --> 06:31.223
How long?

06:31.290 --> 06:33.383
I'm not sure yet, sweetheart.

06:34.694 --> 06:36.662
Who's gonna take me to school?

06:36.729 --> 06:39.926
I am. In fact, I got everything ready.

06:39.999 --> 06:43.958
I made your lunch
and I packed your backpack. Yummy.

06:45.872 --> 06:48.204
You cut my PB and J sideways.

06:48.608 --> 06:51.304
Carrie cuts it in half. I like it cut in half.

06:52.111 --> 06:55.274
Well, it tastes the same
both ways, I promise.

06:55.348 --> 06:58.681
Katie Brown's mom
cuts her sandwiches sideways

06:58.751 --> 07:00.912
and she's always trying to kiss me.

07:01.254 --> 07:02.346
Yuck.

07:02.422 --> 07:04.356
- Daddy!
- Hey.

07:07.160 --> 07:09.594
Jamie, can you go upstairs
for a few minutes, sweetheart?

07:09.662 --> 07:11.425
- Why?
- Hey, why don't you go upstairs

07:11.497 --> 07:12.759
and fire up the PlayStation?

07:12.832 --> 07:15.164
Mommy's gonna let you play for
10 minutes before you go to school.

07:15.234 --> 07:16.758
- Sweet.
- Sweet.

07:21.307 --> 07:24.765
Look, I have to go to Dan's parole
hearing, but before I do,

07:24.844 --> 07:27.369
- I need you to hear me out.
- Dan's up for parole?

07:27.447 --> 07:29.813
He pled guilty to second-degree murder.

07:29.882 --> 07:33.716
He served good time
and it's been about five years, so, yeah.

07:33.953 --> 07:35.284
That's not why I'm here.

07:37.490 --> 07:39.185
All right, I'm listening.

07:40.126 --> 07:43.562
There is absolutely nothing going on
between me and Carrie.

07:43.963 --> 07:45.089
Didn't look like nothing.

07:45.164 --> 07:47.189
Haley, she's got some kind of weird crush

07:47.266 --> 07:49.734
and she thinks the feeling's mutual,
but it's not.

07:49.802 --> 07:52.532
There was some flirting
and I let it go and I shouldn't have,

07:52.605 --> 07:55.073
but I swear to you, that's all there was.

07:55.575 --> 07:58.100
- What else, Nathan?
- Nothing.

07:58.344 --> 08:02.781
I just... I mean, I guess I knew
that she was getting attached.

08:03.249 --> 08:05.911
I was gonna say something to you, okay?
I was, but...

08:05.985 --> 08:09.250
I just need you to know that there is
nothing going on between us.

08:09.322 --> 08:11.085
Damn it, Nathan.

08:12.792 --> 08:17.729
I really thought we were, like, rounding
this corner of everything, you know?

08:17.997 --> 08:20.488
I don't... I don't know how to...

08:20.900 --> 08:23.835
I just, I need some time to think
and just be alone.

08:23.903 --> 08:25.768
Haley, please, just...

08:28.474 --> 08:31.602
Can you just...
Can you just go to Dan's hearing,

08:32.078 --> 08:35.535
and then we can find a time
to deal with this later?

08:37.650 --> 08:38.981
Please?

08:42.455 --> 08:43.785
Okay.

08:49.462 --> 08:50.827
Nathan.

08:56.669 --> 08:58.569
There better not be more.

09:06.479 --> 09:09.414
I will be damned if I let you
steal my artist, John.

09:09.482 --> 09:11.473
It's not stealing if she wants it to happen.

09:11.551 --> 09:12.916
Did she say that?

09:14.020 --> 09:17.114
What did you tell her?
A bunch of lies to make her feel that way?

09:17.189 --> 09:19.555
Like you did with that little actress
out in LA? How'd that go?

09:19.625 --> 09:22.150
Oh, admittedly,
that could have gone better.

09:22.628 --> 09:26.428
See, I heard you convinced her
to quit her hit TV show

09:26.499 --> 09:28.729
in order to tour for this record.

09:28.801 --> 09:30.860
But I guess your ghostwriter
and your cool producer

09:30.937 --> 09:32.404
didn't really work out, did they?

09:32.471 --> 09:37.033
Because now, thanks to you, she doesn't
have a music career or a TV show.

09:37.777 --> 09:40.644
John, you forget, I worked for you
for two years, okay?

09:40.713 --> 09:44.979
I watched you churn and burn all your
artists in your corporate greed machine.

09:45.217 --> 09:49.244
And I will not let that happen to Mia.
She deserves way better than that.

09:49.956 --> 09:51.548
Are you finished?

09:54.093 --> 09:55.993
That's a nice speech, Peyton.

09:56.562 --> 10:00.794
The only question is,
can you back it up? Huh?

10:01.667 --> 10:04.158
You got a lot of great albums on that wall.

10:04.403 --> 10:06.963
But the sad truth is, you wouldn't
have heard of half of them

10:07.039 --> 10:09.803
without the support of a major label.
I should know.

10:09.875 --> 10:11.706
I signed four of them.

10:12.178 --> 10:14.908
You know what? Mia's gonna make it.
We'll be just fine.

10:14.981 --> 10:16.573
Are you sure?

10:17.516 --> 10:19.381
Just look at that wall again.

10:19.585 --> 10:21.985
All those artists have two things
in common.

10:22.054 --> 10:24.648
Great songs and a major label.

10:26.525 --> 10:28.686
I'll be honest, I'd love to sign Mia.

10:28.761 --> 10:32.288
I wanna get her music out there
into the world, because it is great.

10:32.365 --> 10:33.832
She deserves to be heard

10:33.899 --> 10:36.891
and you do not have the resources
to do that yet.

10:36.969 --> 10:38.869
You're not even close.

10:40.673 --> 10:42.470
You're just gonna kill her.

10:43.809 --> 10:47.540
Here. I'm in town until tomorrow morning.

10:49.715 --> 10:51.979
Do the right thing, Sawyer.

10:54.387 --> 10:58.448
<i>(TELL ME HOWBY</i> SARA LOV
PLAYING ON SOUNDTRACK)

11:04.597 --> 11:07.225
<i>I know</i>
<i>We can talk about it later</i>

11:07.299 --> 11:10.063
Mitchell, sub in for Q.

11:11.303 --> 11:14.204
Man, why you pulling me, Coach?
Come on.

11:14.340 --> 11:16.274
Let me see your hand.

11:22.948 --> 11:24.210
(GASPING)

11:26.452 --> 11:30.218
All right, we'll get a doctor to take
a look at that. Grab some pine.

11:43.803 --> 11:44.963
Jamie.

11:47.707 --> 11:49.470
Jamie.

11:57.349 --> 11:59.544
Why are you sad, Nanny Carrie?

11:59.618 --> 12:03.679
Well, I'm sad because I have to go away.

12:04.590 --> 12:06.649
But I don't want you to go away.

12:06.726 --> 12:08.159
Why do you have to leave?

12:08.227 --> 12:11.355
I really don't wanna leave you, it's just...

12:12.231 --> 12:15.598
Your mommy doesn't like Nanny Carrie.
She wants me to leave.

12:15.868 --> 12:17.768
But I want you to stay.

12:18.604 --> 12:19.832
So do I.

12:20.806 --> 12:23.707
But your mom's the boss
and what she says goes.

12:28.514 --> 12:32.348
I wish you were my little boy.
I always will.

12:37.456 --> 12:39.424
Goodbye, Jamie.

12:40.392 --> 12:43.293
<i>Tell me how</i>

12:44.430 --> 12:47.092
<i>Tell me how</i>

12:48.400 --> 12:49.594
<i>Tell me how</i>

12:49.668 --> 12:53.502
Okay, you have 4,000 square feet
on Central Park West.

12:53.572 --> 12:55.665
- Mmm-hmm.
- What's this place?

12:55.741 --> 13:00.007
Well, this place is a good investment.

13:03.349 --> 13:07.115
And it doubles as a crash pad when
I want to party in the East Village.

13:12.792 --> 13:14.623
Somebody's here.

13:40.986 --> 13:42.613
- Rachel.
- Brooke, get a shower running.

13:42.688 --> 13:44.019
Make it cold. I'm gonna need some towels.

13:44.089 --> 13:46.922
Rachel. Rachel, can you hear me?
Brooke. Shower. Now.

13:46.992 --> 13:49.358
- Okay.
- Come on.

13:49.428 --> 13:51.760
Come on, Rachel. Come on.
Come on, baby. Come on.

13:51.831 --> 13:55.062
Come on, baby. Baby, come on.
Wake up. Rachel, wake up.

13:55.134 --> 13:57.261
Come on, come on. Wake up.
Open your eyes.

13:57.336 --> 13:59.998
Open your eyes, sweetie.
Come on. Come on.

14:00.539 --> 14:04.703
Wake up! Wake up, come on.
Come on, wake up.

14:04.810 --> 14:07.176
- Please don't let her die.
- Come on, wake up! Come on, baby.

14:07.246 --> 14:10.147
Baby, wake up. Rachel.
Rachel, open your eyes!

14:10.216 --> 14:14.516
Open your eyes! Wake up!
Please, wake up!

14:17.523 --> 14:22.460
<i>(RIGHTHERE WITH YOU</i> BY FROZEN
FLAMES PLAYING ON SOUNDTRACK)

14:26.198 --> 14:28.689
Please tell me she's gonna be okay.

14:32.238 --> 14:35.435
If by "okay" you mean
"she's not gonna die," then, yes.

14:36.208 --> 14:37.937
But, no, she's not okay.

14:39.612 --> 14:41.443
Do I need to take her
to the emergency room?

14:41.513 --> 14:46.007
Her color's back, she's breathing,
she's out of any immediate danger.

14:46.485 --> 14:50.046
Just let me keep an eye on her
a little bit longer. We'll see.

14:50.122 --> 14:51.111
Okay.

14:53.359 --> 14:55.350
How do you know her?

14:56.128 --> 14:59.689
She's a friend from home.
I hired her to model for the company.

14:59.765 --> 15:01.596
Haven't seen her in a while.

15:02.601 --> 15:05.399
I knew she had problems, but not like this.

15:07.206 --> 15:12.940
She started screwing up photo shoots,
and Victoria insisted I let her go.

15:15.514 --> 15:17.846
I need to help her. What do I do?

15:17.917 --> 15:19.817
Start by getting rid of this.

15:20.452 --> 15:22.352
Don't put it in the trash.

15:22.988 --> 15:24.182
Why?

15:24.256 --> 15:27.054
When she wakes up,
that's the first place she'll look.

15:28.894 --> 15:32.853
<i>Who are you to judge me?</i>

15:35.000 --> 15:35.989
Okay.

15:37.169 --> 15:39.330
Well, I'm afraid it's not good.

15:39.405 --> 15:43.136
You have a hairline fracture
of your right carpal radius.

15:44.343 --> 15:45.367
What's that mean?

15:45.444 --> 15:49.437
Well, it means you need a cast on that
wrist for the next four to six weeks.

15:49.515 --> 15:51.881
Man, I can't do that. I'm gonna
miss too many games, man, I'm...

15:51.951 --> 15:54.511
You know what,
this is my last season, okay?

15:54.586 --> 15:57.987
To impress the scouts if I wanna
play college ball. All right?

15:58.090 --> 15:59.489
Help me out, man.

15:59.725 --> 16:03.627
You need the cast on.
You don't have a choice. I'm sorry.

16:10.669 --> 16:13.968
Hey, baby. How was your day at school?

16:18.644 --> 16:20.077
What's wrong, Jamie?

16:20.145 --> 16:22.579
Why did Nanny Carrie have to go away?

16:24.083 --> 16:25.243
Um...

16:25.985 --> 16:27.646
Little man, you know, with grownups

16:27.720 --> 16:31.349
sometimes they just need to
move on with their own lives.

16:31.423 --> 16:36.486
And Nanny Carrie decided that it
was time to move on with her life.

16:36.562 --> 16:38.086
That's not what she said.

16:38.163 --> 16:41.132
She said you sent her away
'cause you hated her.

16:41.266 --> 16:42.961
- She didn't wanna go.
- Wait, wait, wait, wait.

16:43.035 --> 16:44.832
When did she tell you this?

16:45.404 --> 16:46.996
Today at school.

16:47.072 --> 16:53.102
<i>Who are you to make me feel this way?</i>

16:53.178 --> 16:56.204
The man is a complete snake.
I've seen him do it a thousand times.

16:56.281 --> 16:58.545
He offers you the moon
and throws you out there

16:58.617 --> 17:01.882
and the second you fall short
he drops you just like that.

17:01.954 --> 17:03.387
Look, I don't care about him.

17:03.455 --> 17:06.288
I love this record
and I'm sure we'll be okay.

17:06.358 --> 17:07.790
No, we will. You're right. We will be okay.

17:07.859 --> 17:10.454
We'll be better than okay, and you know
why? Because I've got a plan.

17:10.529 --> 17:12.792
We're gonna roll out
your first single on college radio,

17:12.865 --> 17:15.628
we'll get you out there on tour,
then we'll do guerilla marketing,

17:15.701 --> 17:18.670
like flyers and wild postings
in all the mass markets.

17:18.737 --> 17:21.103
Oh, and I've got a lot
of street-team contacts out in LA

17:21.173 --> 17:22.663
that I know would love to work with you.

17:22.741 --> 17:24.709
That sounds great.

17:24.777 --> 17:28.008
No. No, it doesn't, Mia.

17:28.079 --> 17:32.073
God, he's offering you, like,
a five-course meal up in first class

17:32.151 --> 17:34.119
and I'm offering you a sandwich in coach.

17:34.186 --> 17:36.450
No, Peyton, don't feel that way. I don't.

17:36.522 --> 17:37.716
But it's true, honey, okay?

17:37.790 --> 17:39.781
You made a much better record
than I thought you could,

17:39.858 --> 17:44.420
and you deserve the spot on the big tour
and the kind of airplay and big promotion

17:44.496 --> 17:46.430
that I just, I can't give it to you.

17:46.498 --> 17:48.329
No. It doesn't matter.

17:48.400 --> 17:51.563
You're the one who got me here
and I wanna stay with you.

17:53.572 --> 17:56.507
- You really mean that?
- Absolutely.

17:57.943 --> 18:00.878
<i>Right here with you</i>

18:00.946 --> 18:01.935
Okay.

18:02.014 --> 18:03.777
<i>Right here with you</i>

18:09.822 --> 18:11.949
- I need to get my stuff.
- It's in the garage.

18:12.024 --> 18:14.720
Boxes are marked "whore."
I'll have the keys now.

18:15.294 --> 18:18.161
I'm sorry, Haley.
I never meant for it to turn out this way.

18:18.230 --> 18:20.391
Did you go by Jamie's school today?

18:20.632 --> 18:23.396
Jamie looks at me as family.
I was just saying goodbye.

18:23.469 --> 18:27.269
No. You are not family.
I invited you into this home,

18:27.339 --> 18:29.603
and I trusted you with the two
most important things in my life.

18:29.675 --> 18:32.439
My husband and my son,
and you betrayed that trust.

18:32.511 --> 18:34.069
I know you're upset.

18:34.179 --> 18:38.047
Just know that I never meant
for Nathan to fall in love with me.

18:40.219 --> 18:44.883
Oh, honey. He's not in love with you,
I can promise you that.

18:46.592 --> 18:48.492
Did he tell you he kissed me?

18:49.461 --> 18:50.587
Hmm.

18:50.829 --> 18:54.663
He didn't tell you, did he?
God, that is so Nathan.

18:54.733 --> 18:59.830
Well, he did kiss me and he watched me
swim naked and he liked it.

19:00.105 --> 19:02.573
You see, he wanted me in that shower.

19:02.641 --> 19:05.132
I'm sorry that it's hard for you
to face, but it's the truth.

19:05.210 --> 19:08.407
I have told you once
and I am not gonna tell you again.

19:08.480 --> 19:11.040
Stay the hell away from my family!

19:13.819 --> 19:15.343
I hate you!

19:17.589 --> 19:18.783
Jamie.

19:28.367 --> 19:29.925
Well, well.

19:31.336 --> 19:32.394
Am I dead?

19:33.205 --> 19:34.832
You OD'ed.

19:36.074 --> 19:38.941
You're alive, but you're really stupid.

19:41.079 --> 19:43.604
Rachel, what happened to you?

19:44.116 --> 19:45.344
I don't know.

19:46.852 --> 19:48.717
Life happened, I guess.

19:51.123 --> 19:52.420
Drugs?

19:55.060 --> 19:56.618
Just made me feel better.

19:58.564 --> 20:00.589
Then they just made me feel.

20:01.233 --> 20:04.862
Why didn't you come to me?
Why didn't you let me help you?

20:08.407 --> 20:10.170
We were friends, Brooke.

20:13.645 --> 20:15.545
You fired me.

20:26.425 --> 20:28.154
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

20:39.404 --> 20:40.462
Who is it?

20:40.539 --> 20:43.702
Brooke, lock the door.
Don't come out till I say.

20:45.611 --> 20:46.908
(DOOR CLOSING)

20:55.821 --> 20:58.051
- Hey, man, come on in.
- Who are you?

20:58.123 --> 21:00.853
Oh, it's cool, Rachel said
you were gonna be stopping by.

21:00.926 --> 21:02.757
Come on in, man. Come on.

21:02.828 --> 21:04.819
We're all in the waiting room here.

21:07.833 --> 21:11.132
So, where's Rachel?

21:11.203 --> 21:14.138
She's... She's right here.

21:17.542 --> 21:19.840
Let me go, man. I didn't do nothing to you.

21:19.911 --> 21:22.004
Yeah, well, my friend is falling out
on your junk back there.

21:22.080 --> 21:25.243
- So, where is it?
- I don't know what you're talking about.

21:27.486 --> 21:29.716
You ever come in here again,
I will break your neck.

21:29.788 --> 21:31.415
- Do you hear me?
- Yeah. Yeah.

21:37.229 --> 21:39.129
That bitch owes me a lot of money, man!

21:39.197 --> 21:41.665
Yeah? Consider that payment in full.

21:42.668 --> 21:44.033
Get the hell out of here.

21:49.741 --> 21:51.470
Owen, who was that?

21:52.411 --> 21:54.140
Nobody that's coming back.

21:54.880 --> 21:59.214
<i>(SEE THESE BONES</i> BY NADA SURF
PLAYING ON SOUNDTRACK)

21:59.484 --> 22:01.384
So, how'd it go with Haley?

22:01.553 --> 22:03.077
She's gonna need more time.

22:03.155 --> 22:05.521
Well, give it to her. You owe her that.

22:08.727 --> 22:11.787
I just wish he would've helped us more,
you know?

22:12.197 --> 22:14.256
It would've been really nice
to have a father today.

22:14.333 --> 22:16.858
Someone I could actually
turn to for advice.

22:17.235 --> 22:20.227
Yeah. You know, for the past four years,

22:20.772 --> 22:24.708
I've pretended that Dan didn't exist.
Then I get this letter and it hits me.

22:24.776 --> 22:28.337
That one day, we may have to face
having him in our lives again.

22:30.782 --> 22:32.977
Let's not let that be today.

22:33.885 --> 22:36.319
<i>Look alive</i>

22:36.388 --> 22:39.084
<i>See these bones</i>

22:41.226 --> 22:46.528
<i>What you are now we were once</i>

22:48.400 --> 22:51.767
<i>Try as they might, no one's immune to</i>

22:51.970 --> 22:55.599
<i>Misfiring and acting on the wrong clues</i>

22:55.674 --> 22:57.608
Hello, Son.

22:57.676 --> 22:59.473
<i>And thinking it's time to redo and redo</i>

23:01.980 --> 23:06.349
<i>I feel rain in the movies and the talk</i>
<i>before the screen lights</i>

23:06.585 --> 23:09.486
<i>I hear strings in the park</i>

23:09.621 --> 23:11.088
<i>I don't like to call her right</i>

23:11.189 --> 23:14.920
Hello, Peyton.
I was pretty sure I'd be hearing from you.

23:15.527 --> 23:20.521
Well, I thought about what you said
and I think you're right about Mia.

23:20.899 --> 23:25.063
So the assistant to the assistant
finally learns the business.

23:25.170 --> 23:27.604
Congratulations, Peyton. It's about time.

23:27.672 --> 23:29.299
About time for what?

23:31.042 --> 23:35.376
Mia, it really is in your best interest.

23:36.548 --> 23:38.277
That's not what you said earlier today.

23:38.383 --> 23:41.045
You said that he was an evil snake
that couldn't be trusted.

23:41.153 --> 23:42.313
So, which is it, Peyton?

23:42.387 --> 23:45.288
In spite of what she said earlier,
I think you should listen to her now, Mia.

23:45.357 --> 23:46.619
She's making a lot of sense.

23:46.691 --> 23:48.659
Oh, really? She's making sense now?

23:48.727 --> 23:50.957
Listen, you can do whatever deal
you want with her.

23:51.029 --> 23:53.259
Just know that I will
never play for you. Never.

23:53.331 --> 23:56.198
I'm an artist, not a business transaction.

23:57.769 --> 24:01.500
You know, Peyton, I really thought
we had something special.

24:02.307 --> 24:04.332
Thanks for selling me out.

24:04.709 --> 24:05.971
No, Mia.

24:06.878 --> 24:08.209
Mia, wait.

24:08.280 --> 24:09.713
(DOOR SLAMMING)

24:16.788 --> 24:18.255
Afternoon.

24:20.025 --> 24:22.755
When I was 17 years old, I fell in love.

24:23.662 --> 24:27.826
Her name was Karen and for a long time,
she loved me back.

24:29.067 --> 24:34.733
We had a son, Lucas, but we never became
the family we should have been.

24:36.441 --> 24:38.932
Instead, my brother Keith
assumed that role.

24:41.813 --> 24:43.804
And in my heart something died.

24:44.549 --> 24:46.107
I deserve to be in here.

24:46.184 --> 24:48.448
There's no excuse
for the crime that I committed.

24:48.520 --> 24:51.887
And believe me when I tell you
I spend every moment

24:51.957 --> 24:54.482
wishing I could take that fateful day back.

24:56.495 --> 24:59.089
Keith Scott is dead because of me.

24:59.931 --> 25:03.526
And that's something I have to live with
for the rest of my life.

25:03.935 --> 25:05.994
So I'll just make one pledge here today.

25:06.071 --> 25:08.869
If at some time you decide
to grant me my freedom,

25:09.007 --> 25:12.602
know that I'll spend every living moment
trying to mend the lives

25:12.677 --> 25:15.077
of the people that I hurt by my actions.

25:15.213 --> 25:18.341
<i>(CA TARACTS</i> BY ANDREW BIRD
PLAYING ON SOUNDTRACK)

25:18.416 --> 25:20.782
Because I've lost more than my freedom.

25:22.787 --> 25:25.585
I've lost something
far more important than that.

25:27.759 --> 25:28.953
A family.

25:30.328 --> 25:32.990
These young men stand at the dawn
of their adult lives.

25:33.064 --> 25:38.468
So far, because of what I've put them
through, they've had it pretty rough.

25:39.704 --> 25:41.035
They deserve better.

25:42.474 --> 25:43.998
They deserve a father.

25:47.145 --> 25:49.238
I hope someday you'll give them that.

25:50.682 --> 25:52.411
Thank you, Mr. Scott.

25:53.952 --> 25:56.546
Does anyone else
wish to speak at this time?

25:57.422 --> 26:00.880
Yes. I'm Lucas Scott.

26:02.160 --> 26:03.855
I'm his son.

26:03.962 --> 26:05.293
Please, go ahead.

26:05.363 --> 26:08.764
My father abandoned my mother
when she was pregnant with me.

26:08.833 --> 26:13.133
He left us to struggle on our own,
even though he was a man of means.

26:14.472 --> 26:17.839
Growing up,
I only had one person to look after me.

26:19.578 --> 26:20.977
Keith Scott.

26:24.950 --> 26:27.111
And this man killed him.

26:27.986 --> 26:32.548
His own brother, in cold blood
at point-blank range.

26:33.892 --> 26:36.190
Next week, I'm getting married.

26:36.928 --> 26:41.024
Keith would have been my best man.

26:42.133 --> 26:43.725
But he's not gonna be there,

26:43.802 --> 26:46.430
just like he wasn't there
to see my state championship

26:46.504 --> 26:48.836
or see my first novel published.

26:50.709 --> 26:52.438
Dan took all that.

26:53.178 --> 26:55.578
He did it with malice and premeditation.

26:56.915 --> 27:02.080
Dan is an educated man
and if he's nothing, he's very persuasive.

27:04.322 --> 27:06.051
Do not let him fool you.

27:08.760 --> 27:11.957
He has a very dark and ugly heart.

27:13.131 --> 27:17.090
And he should never be allowed
to walk the streets a free man.

27:18.236 --> 27:21.899
So as you deliberate his fate,
I ask you only one question.

27:21.973 --> 27:24.032
How can a father hope
to influence his sons

27:24.109 --> 27:27.044
when they never even came to see him?

27:30.548 --> 27:32.311
Never even once.

27:37.022 --> 27:38.353
Thank you.

27:39.290 --> 27:40.655
Actually,

27:42.027 --> 27:47.488
it looks here that, Nathan,
you've been to visit your father recently.

27:50.235 --> 27:51.600
Is that true?

27:54.472 --> 27:55.530
Yes.

28:09.654 --> 28:11.281
What the hell?

28:12.090 --> 28:15.082
You went to go see Dan
and you didn't tell me. Why?

28:15.260 --> 28:17.956
'Cause I was done with him
and I wanted to tell him to his face.

28:18.029 --> 28:19.053
I didn't think it mattered.

28:19.130 --> 28:20.597
Well, it did matter.

28:20.665 --> 28:23.998
Just like getting up there and telling them
who he really is mattered.

28:24.202 --> 28:26.670
- Don't you get it?
- Get what?

28:26.738 --> 28:30.572
If they think you still need Dan
in your life, they might let him out.

28:32.744 --> 28:36.805
You know, it's not me I'm worried about.
Or you. It's Jamie.

28:37.882 --> 28:40.442
Dan's gonna try to get to him.
You know that.

28:41.419 --> 28:45.150
The only way to keep your family safe
is if Dan stays locked up.

28:49.461 --> 28:51.622
<i>(THE FILM DID NOTGO ROUND</i> BY NADA
SURF PLAYING ON SOUNDTRACK)

28:51.696 --> 28:53.664
Can I ask you something?

28:55.800 --> 28:57.768
How'd you know who the guy was

28:57.936 --> 29:00.063
and what to do with Rachel?

29:00.839 --> 29:03.171
Let's just say I've been there.

29:03.408 --> 29:05.308
You mean you had a problem?

29:05.376 --> 29:06.468
No.

29:08.213 --> 29:10.238
I'm saying I'm an addict.

29:10.682 --> 29:12.309
A junkie, Brooke.

29:14.352 --> 29:17.913
You ever wonder why you never
see me take a drink behind the bar?

29:19.891 --> 29:22.018
Been sober eight years.

29:23.361 --> 29:24.953
How'd you make it back?

29:25.063 --> 29:27.554
Had a friend. He helped me.

29:27.665 --> 29:30.259
I'd be dead right now if it wasn't for him,
no question.

29:30.335 --> 29:32.030
He never gave up on me.

29:34.806 --> 29:38.606
See, Brooke, I can understand the whole
cutting off Rachel on the business side,

29:38.676 --> 29:40.667
but I'm struggling
with the whole friendship side.

29:40.745 --> 29:42.474
You don't know my mother.

29:42.881 --> 29:46.009
Victoria is relentless
when she wants something,

29:46.084 --> 29:48.985
and it's easier to just do it
than to fight her.

29:49.053 --> 29:51.317
You ever wonder where you'd be
if at some critical moment

29:51.389 --> 29:55.621
when you needed it the most,
your friends just weren't there for you?

29:58.129 --> 30:00.495
<i>I hate to see you go</i>

30:00.565 --> 30:02.396
Can she ever be okay again?

30:02.467 --> 30:04.298
I don't know. Maybe.

30:04.369 --> 30:09.602
You know, what Rachel needs right now
is to go to rehab.

30:10.708 --> 30:12.835
This is the place that helped me.

30:12.911 --> 30:15.607
They've got a facility here,
it's the best in the city.

30:19.050 --> 30:21.917
And I can take her there for you,
if you need me to.

30:22.887 --> 30:24.479
I need to do it.

30:26.124 --> 30:28.649
I have to step up for her. She needs me.

30:29.894 --> 30:33.352
In that case, I'm gonna go.

30:36.901 --> 30:40.132
Do not give up on her, Brooke.
You are better than that.

30:42.407 --> 30:46.275
<i>You showed me just</i>
<i>how easy love could be</i>

30:51.149 --> 30:52.241
Some first date, huh?

30:52.317 --> 30:53.306
(OWEN LAUGHING)

30:53.418 --> 30:55.511
Is that what this was?

30:56.087 --> 30:58.988
You know, I have to say,
your life is really impressive.

30:59.057 --> 31:02.026
The real estate, the business, the money...

31:03.795 --> 31:05.660
It's just not what really interests me.

31:07.599 --> 31:11.660
<i>Everyone's gotta leave their love sometime</i>

31:11.736 --> 31:14.227
What's under all the clothes,
Brooke Davis?

31:14.305 --> 31:17.934
<i>If not now, then at the end of your lifetime</i>

31:18.042 --> 31:19.600
(DOOR CLOSING)

31:28.186 --> 31:32.589
<i>You'll be waiting by my bed, I know</i>

31:32.924 --> 31:34.551
NATHAN: Didn't expect to find you here.

31:34.626 --> 31:36.355
Oh, you know...

31:37.028 --> 31:38.791
Ain't nothing like an empty gym
when you wanna be

31:38.863 --> 31:40.660
alone with your thoughts, man.

31:43.034 --> 31:45.594
- What you doing here?
- The same.

31:48.606 --> 31:50.301
What's on your mind?

31:50.375 --> 31:54.368
Oh, man, just planning my big move
on your scoring title.

31:56.347 --> 31:59.839
Man, that... That last season you had.
Boy, that...

31:59.918 --> 32:02.216
That must have been something special.

32:03.488 --> 32:07.720
Truth be told,
I took it for granted a little bit.

32:07.792 --> 32:11.751
I mean, breaking all those records
and the scouts coming to see me play,

32:11.829 --> 32:13.490
the state championship...

32:15.166 --> 32:16.724
I wish I could go back.

32:17.535 --> 32:19.696
I'd appreciate it more.

32:22.607 --> 32:25.906
I just want it so bad, man. You know?

32:27.679 --> 32:29.977
- Is that okay to say? 'Cause I...
- Sure.

32:31.449 --> 32:33.144
And you'll get there.

32:33.851 --> 32:37.548
And when you do, just be sure to enjoy it.

32:37.622 --> 32:41.422
'Cause it only comes once.
In the blink of an eye, it can all be gone.

32:46.898 --> 32:52.495
<i>I touch these strings</i>
<i>but cannot touch the sound</i>

33:00.845 --> 33:02.574
You gotta trust me, Rachel.

33:02.647 --> 33:06.105
This is the best rehab facility in the city
and I'm gonna take care of everything.

33:06.184 --> 33:08.118
I don't care what it costs.

33:08.186 --> 33:11.383
Please, Brooke. Please, I don't wanna
be alone again, all right?

33:11.456 --> 33:12.980
I don't wanna go to some strange place.

33:13.057 --> 33:15.252
I'll be good, I promise. I'll stop.

33:15.393 --> 33:17.088
Honey, we both know that's not realistic.

33:17.161 --> 33:20.790
You have a problem and you need to go.

33:22.967 --> 33:25.527
Brooke, you're my only friend.

33:26.671 --> 33:29.504
If you leave me this time, I won't make it.

33:31.976 --> 33:33.739
Please don't give up on me.

33:33.811 --> 33:36.177
Can't I just stay here with you?

33:54.532 --> 33:56.659
- Hey.
- Hey.

33:56.801 --> 34:00.168
Look, man, I'm sorry about
what happened today with Dan.

34:00.505 --> 34:03.030
I let you down.
I could have done better, I just...

34:03.107 --> 34:05.200
He got to me. You know?

34:05.910 --> 34:07.639
And I know you're always
looking out for Jamie, just...

34:07.712 --> 34:11.170
You gotta understand, I would never
let anything happen to him.

34:11.315 --> 34:12.782
Then go be his dad.

34:13.284 --> 34:15.275
Work things out with your wife.

34:15.920 --> 34:17.547
It's really bad, man.

34:17.621 --> 34:19.089
Just talk to her, okay?

34:19.157 --> 34:22.524
And remember it might be better to save
your marriage than to be right on this one.

34:22.592 --> 34:24.117
Okay?

34:24.362 --> 34:27.228
I mean, besides, since Haley's gonna
be Lindsey's maid-of-honor,

34:27.297 --> 34:31.063
I'm really gonna need my best man
to be getting along with her.

34:33.538 --> 34:35.005
Wow.

34:35.739 --> 34:39.471
Thanks, man,
I know that was supposed to be Keith.

34:40.143 --> 34:42.203
I'm honored.

34:54.725 --> 34:56.955
Miss you.

35:03.201 --> 35:06.637
Hey, Jim Jam. Time for bed, buddy.
Here we go.

35:07.472 --> 35:11.169
Want me to read you a story?
How about <i>Go, Dog. Go!</i>

35:11.242 --> 35:12.766
You like that one, right?

35:12.844 --> 35:14.334
Where's Daddy?

35:16.481 --> 35:20.008
Mommy and Daddy are just having
a little bit of a tough time right now.

35:20.084 --> 35:22.314
He's staying with Uncle Lucas.

35:22.820 --> 35:26.051
Is Daddy gonna be sad again?
Like last time?

35:26.424 --> 35:28.756
I don't think so. Hope not.

35:29.794 --> 35:33.127
Daddy stopped being sad when
Nanny Carrie came and lived with us.

35:33.297 --> 35:34.889
He liked Nanny Carrie.

35:35.233 --> 35:40.933
I know this is probably really hard for you
to understand 'cause you're so little.

35:42.039 --> 35:45.634
Nanny Carrie wasn't a very nice lady
and she needed to go away.

35:49.447 --> 35:52.109
I wish Nanny Carrie was my mama.

36:05.029 --> 36:06.087
So?

36:08.299 --> 36:10.324
Don't freak out, okay?

36:10.468 --> 36:12.368
But what if I told you
that <i>Only Fooling Myself</i>

36:12.436 --> 36:14.700
is gonna be your first single?

36:17.208 --> 36:20.268
Your record will be distributed nationally
in six weeks.

36:20.344 --> 36:24.576
You will stay on Red Bedroom Records,
which John will now distribute worldwide.

36:24.649 --> 36:28.517
You have final say on touring,
image rights and album art,

36:28.586 --> 36:32.682
and you get to keep your publishing,
which means you own all your own songs.

36:33.090 --> 36:34.216
And?

36:34.292 --> 36:36.487
And we get to stay together as a team.

36:36.561 --> 36:39.587
- You did it!
- No, you did it with that performance!

36:39.664 --> 36:43.532
That was incredible. Dude, did you see
his face when you freaked out on him?

36:43.601 --> 36:47.401
It was awesome. He was practically
tripping over himself to give us this deal.

36:47.471 --> 36:50.998
You know, it wasn't that hard a
performance. I meant every word.

36:51.409 --> 36:54.173
Except the part when I called
you a sell-out, not that part.

36:55.813 --> 37:00.079
Well, I think you've gotta go home
and pack your bags now,

37:00.151 --> 37:02.551
'cause you're opening up
in Houston tomorrow.

37:02.620 --> 37:03.882
- What?
- Yeah, and for someone

37:03.955 --> 37:07.288
who I think that you know.
Have you heard of Ryan Adams?

37:07.358 --> 37:09.826
Oh, my God! That's amazing.

37:13.397 --> 37:15.388
Wait, what? What's wrong?

37:15.833 --> 37:19.360
Oh, it's just... It all happened so fast.

37:19.470 --> 37:21.904
I'm not sure I'm ready to say goodbye.

37:21.973 --> 37:23.565
No, you're ready.

37:25.176 --> 37:29.135
And it's not goodbye. This is just the
beginning of your dream come true.

37:30.381 --> 37:34.147
And I want you to know, I am really,
really proud to be a part of it.

37:34.785 --> 37:36.719
Now go out there and be great.

37:37.922 --> 37:38.911
Okay.

37:44.061 --> 37:48.589
<i>(BESTNOT TO THINKABOUTIT</i>
BY ATHLETE PLAYING ON SOUNDTRACK)

